TI  - Inland dry season saline intrusion in the Vietnamese Mekong River Delta is driving the identification and implementation of alternative crops to rice
T2  - AGRICULTURAL SYSTEMS
LA  - English
KW  - Inland saline intrusion is causing substantial rice losses during the dry season of the Mekong River Delta
KW  - Vietnam
KW  - Alternative crops and management practices need to be identified to provide farmers with options to supplement the loss of rice income
KW  - Numerous biophysical
KW  - environmental
KW  - and socioeconomic factors are identified that help determine an alternative crops suitability
KW  - Management practices including mulching
KW  - raised beds and soil water monitoring can decrease salinity stress and improve water use efficiency
KW  - Combining alternative crops and management practices provide farmers with production options for saline affected areas during the dry season
KW  - WATER-USE EFFICIENCY
KW  - CHENOPODIUM-QUINOA WILLD.
